  "caption": "India's PCB market isn't just growing. It's accelerating.\n\nHere's the data that every hardware founder and product designer in India should know.\n\n$7.26 billion in 2025. Projected $25.48 billion by 2034. That's a 15% CAGR.\n\nWhat's fueling this?\n\n5G infrastructure rollout creating massive demand for high frequency boards. EV adoption driving need for sophisticated battery management PCBs. India becoming the world's second largest mobile phone manufacturer. And the PLI scheme putting real money behind domestic production.\n\nThe shift from import dependent to manufacturing powerhouse is happening now.\n\nAt Cu Circuits, we're proud to be part of this transformation, building PCBs right here in Chennai.\n\nBookmark this for your next pitch deck.\n\n#PCB #IndiaManufacturing #MakeInIndia #CuCircuits #EVs #5G #PLIScheme #HardwareStartup",
